headline: Infrastructure investing is firing on 'every single cylinder'
summary: When Wall Street talks about investment into US infrastructure, the future of AI data centers is usually at the top of investors' minds these days. Goldman Sachs Chairman of Infrastructure Goldman Sachs Alternatives Philippe Camu discusses with Market Catalysts host Julie Hyman the value of private investment into infrastructure — digital and traditional, like roads, airports, and shipping ports — as an asset class. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Catalysts.
